704378f-a.text:
17 Fleet Street, at the N.E. corner of Willoughby Street (right), showing a 3-story building whose store is occupied by a colored organization, St. John's Fire Baptist Church of Christ in America. On the left appears a view eastward on Fleet Street. In the background is the Myrtle Ave. (B.M.T.)
Elevated. line, and beyond it an old church building.
July 22, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
